text: Cyrielle Banet (born 29 August 1994) is a French rugby union player. She played for the France women's national rugby union team. She was in the 2018 Women's Six Nations Championship and 2020 Women's Six Nations Championship. She played for Montpellier rugby club. == References == Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:French rugby union players
